{"index": 866, "title": "\u00a3115k Software Engineering Leadership Role (60% Hands-on)", "job_location": "London Area, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Hands-on (60%) Leadership role - Ruby on Rails - Hybrid in Shoreditch This role is paying up to \u00a3115k This is a fantastic opportunity for a friendly and experienced leader to join a super interesting company in the leisure/travel industry \u2728They're open to interviewing a range of backgrounds. Whether you're a hands-on Engineering Manager right now or a Tech Lead with people management experience, or even a Senior Engineer who has always got involved in the management stuff, this one could be for you.You will be supporting the team as they embark on building a new booking engine for their platform and completing the transition away from .NET to Ruby on Rails version 8, which is well underway.Essential to know:Hands-on Ruby on Rails experience and frontend experience in your career is essential as you'll be 60% hands-on. The rest of your time will be spent line managing a team of 6 Software Engineers alongside the fractional CTO. The Engineering team consists of mid-senior level Engineers (the most experienced Engineer has 6 yrs) and they really need more hands-on experience on the squad, which is where you come in.6 direct reports. 4 in London consisting of 2 back end using Ruby & 2 front end using Next.js. 2 backend devs in South Africa who are maintaining the previous system built in .NET whilst the transition to Ruby on Rails is finalised.Hybrid in London, Shoreditch 3 days a week \ud83d\udcbcSalary: to \u00a3110k depending on experience & great benefits like 25 days off (+ bank hols), health insurance, company socials, B-corp organisation, and more \ud83e\udd29The company are like the cupid but for luxury holidays - matching clients (usually entrepreneurs, actors, artists, influencers) with unforgettable accommodation & seamless experiences \ud83d\udeebCompany tech environment: Ruby on Rails, Postgres, React