{"index": 891, "title": "Cloud Platform DevOps Engineer GCP", "job_location": "Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Cloud Platform DevOps Engineer GCP Salary: \u00a372,702-\u00a380,780Locations: Manchester, Bristol, Halifax, Leeds & EdinburghHours: Full time (This role will include a requirement to work as part of an on-call rota)Agile Working Options: Hybrid - at least two days per week (40% of your time) in one of our offices. Job DescriptionAt Lloyds Banking Group, we're all driven by our purpose, to Help Britain Prosper. It's why we exist - it's our reason to get out of bed in the morning. The choices we make, our success and our future really matter.But the world is changing fast - and we're changing too. It's never been a more exciting time to join us as we transform our business to shape finance as a force for good. Our teamLloyds Banking Group's goal is to become the biggest Fintech in the UK.Our team is on the journey to create the next generation cloud platform for Lloyds Banking Group that will be at the core of one of the UK's biggest financial service transformationsYou will become part of a product-aligned, highly skilled and motivated engineering team who specialise in GCP networking. Our purpose is to build platform services that enable application teams to rapidly develop and modernise their solutions. About this opportunityWe're looking for an experienced engineer with deep knowledge of Google Cloud networking and a passion for creating secure, reliable, automated infrastructure at scale. You don't need to tick every box - but should recognise yourself in most of the following: Core Skills & Experience\u00b7 Strong hands-on engineering experience with GCP networking in enterprise environments - including core services like VPCs, Cloud Interconnect, VPC Peering, Cloud Routers, Firewalls, DNS, Load balancers, Private Connectivity and Cloud / Hybrid NAT.\u00b7 Terraform expertise and experience deploying infrastructure as code.\u00b7 Practical DevOps experience using modern tooling (e.g., Git, Terraform, Terraform Cloud, GitHub, Harness).\u00b7 Ability to lead by example - whether reviewing code, supporting colleagues, or resolving complex networking issues across production and non-production environments.\u00b7 Strong engineering discipline: designing, deploying, and owning services through their full lifecycle, with security, compliance and reliability built in. About youYou enjoy solving complex, distributed systems challenges and building resilient, automated solutions at scale. You're energised by how cloud networking underpins modern AI, data and hybrid-cloud architectures. Collaborative across teams - architecture, cloud engineering, Google partners - and you care about doing things the right way: secure, observable, automated and resilient. Nice to have (Not required - but great if you have some of them.)\u00b7 Experience maintaining large-scale GCP networking or hybrid connectivity environments.\u00b7 Network Connectivity Centre\u00b7 Understanding of how GCP networking supports key workloads (e.g., Compute, Database, storage, and data/AI platforms).\u00b7 Familiarity with Python or Bash for infrastructure automation.\u00b7 Knowledge of enterprise network concepts such as IP management, proxies, firewalls, Infoblox or identity platforms.\u00b7 Exposure to monitoring and telemetry systems (e.g., Dynatrace, Google Cloud Monitoring).\u00b7 Relevant GCP certifications or a background in cloud/infrastructure engineering. What matters mostCuriosity, ownership, collaboration, and a drive to improve how things work. You'll thrive here if you enjoy shaping solutions, navigating ambiguity, and working with others to deliver secure, scalable, modern cloud networking. About working for us Our focus is to ensure we're inclusive every day, building an organisation that reflects modern society and celebrates diversity in all its forms.We want our people to feel that they belong and can be their best, regardless of background, identity, or culture.If you'd like reasonable adjustments to be made to the recruitment process, please let us know.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": "Hybrid - at least two days per week (40% of your time) in one of our offices.", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Cloud Platform DevOps Engineer GCP", "sen": "LEVEL_2", "tech_raw": "Python, Bash, Terraform, Git, Terraform Cloud, GitHub, Harness, GCP networking, AI", "tech": ["AI_ML"], "comp_raw": "\u00a372,702-\u00a380,780", "comp": "RANGE_75_99K"}}
