{"index": 896, "title": "Technical Support & Field Engineer", "job_location": "Science Central, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Location: Newcastle upon TyneSalary: \u00a326,000\u2013\u00a330,000 per annumType: Full-timeWork Style: Office & Field WorkAbout SPARKSPARK is a fast-growing technology company providing cutting-edge EPoS systems and smart robotics to the hospitality industry across the UK. We are redefining hospitality management through seamless integration of EPoS, online ordering, reservations, loyalty programmes, and AI-driven service automation. Our sleek, modern hardware and user-friendly software platforms are built to improve operational efficiency and enhance the customer experience. Our Robotic Solutions work across a range of industries, from table service robots in restaurants to hotel room service robots all the way to cleaning robots in warehouses.The OpportunityWe\u2019re seeking a Technical Support & Field Engineer to support the deployment, maintenance and servicing of our robotics and EPoS solutions nationwide. This is a hands-on role suited to someone with a technical background, a proactive attitude and a strong interest in robotics or automation.Based in Newcastle, you'll install systems, respond to support requests, and attend customer call-outs. You\u2019ll also help prepare robots for deployment and relay technical insights to our engineering and operations teams.Key ResponsibilitiesInstall and commission robotic and EPoS systems at customer sitesDiagnose and resolve faults both remotely and on-sitePerform routine servicing, firmware updates and minor hardware repairsAssemble, test and configure robots at our facility before deploymentRecord service visits and resolutions accurately for internal trackingSupport onboarding of new clients and act as a technical contact during post-installationAttend urgent call-outs when required, with occasional travel across the UKWhat We\u2019re Looking ForEssentialFull UK driving licence with confidence to travel for site workWorking knowledge of electrical, mechanical or robotic systemsPractical experience using tools and diagnostic equipmentGood communication and customer-facing skillsAbility to work independently and manage your time effectivelyComfortable using IT tools including remote support software and diagnosticsRight to work in the UKDesirableField service, robotics or IT support experienceFamiliarity with automation hardware or PoS systemsBasic networking understanding (e.g. routers, IP, port forwarding)Interest in robotics, mechatronics or embedded systemsEagerness to develop into a mid-level engineering roleWhat You\u2019ll GainJoin a growing team pioneering robotics in hospitalityWork with advanced technologies and automated platformsHybrid work flexibilityTraining and development opportunitiesAnnual performance bonusTravel expense reimbursement for off-site supportApply NowIf you enjoy working with real-world technology, solving problems hands-on and making a direct impact on customers across the UK, we\u2019d love to hear from you.Please send your CV to hr@sparkepos.com\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Science Central, England, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": "Office & Field Work", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": null, "sen": "LEVEL_2", "tech_raw": "EPoS, AI", "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": "\u00a326,000\u2013\u00a330,000 per annum", "comp": "BELOW_45K"}}
