{"index": 900, "title": "Entry Level Technology Consultant", "job_location": "Scotland, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Ey up!What\u2019s that? You love problem solving? Great. Ever thought about a progressive career in the Technology industry? You don\u2019t need any knowledge or a background in Technology to succeed at Ten10. Let\u2019s close the digital skills gap together.Ten10 offers a unique opportunity to explore an exciting future in technology for people from any background. Become a qualified and experienced Software Tester / Business Analyst / Developer / Cyber Security Analyst / Project Manager / Service Desk Analyst / DevOps Engineer with accelerated career progression within one of the world\u2019s most exciting industries. We design, develop, test and launch different apps and systems every day; it's our job to build the best quality tech for our clients and due to the ever-evolving nature of the technology industry, the demand for talent is ever-growing and career development is vast.Every month there are up to 100,000 vacancies in technology and digital roles \u2013 with not enough people to fill them. The Ten10 Academy seeks to close this digital skills gap \u2013 providing you with a role in technology, teaching you not just the skills you would find in a textbook \u2013 but the practical techniques and hands-on experience you need in order to do the job!Honestly, you don't need a techy degree or background to excel; 77% of people who have joined the Academy come from a non-Computing background. We are simply looking for people who have an interest in the Technology industry, like collaborating in teams, enjoy an energetic and adaptable environment and have an aptitude for learning. We need people who will focus on the future and take the initiative, because ultimately, you will determine their own success story - we\u2019re simply here to help you do it!During the recruitment process, we'll tap into your natural aptitude for Tech too, so you can get a taste of whether this is the industry for you.Why Ten10?Ten10 is an established and rapidly growing Technology Consultancy business; we deliver our diverse client portfolio with digital services spanning Development, Testing, Data, DevOps, Service Desk, Project Management, RPA and Business Analysis. We will give you the knowledge, tools and environment to empower you to become the best you can be in a creative and trusting workplace.Ten10 (and the wider world of Tech) is a constantly evolving, fast paced and dynamic environment where we promote a transparent working culture and hard work is rewarded and appreciated. Our culture is very open & friendly and rewards personal performance.What will you be doing?The Academy follows our structured \u2018Learn IT, Grow IT, Live IT\u2019 model across a two-year programme.Learn ITYou\u2019ll begin with a short online course that teaches you the fundamentals of computing, AI and what to expect during training. Next, comes \u2018core\u2019 training; which is an intense 5 week course delivered by our training team (who have all worked as Ten10 Tech Consultants previously). Core training is an introduction to a lot of different technologies, tools and mindsets that are applicable to multiple roles in the technology industry; this means that you\u2019ll have the opportunity to explore and reflect on what you\u2019re naturally good at and what you enjoy; so we can figure out together what sort of roles would be suitable for you in the future.You\u2019ll move into our (free) Academy accommodation for the first 2 weeks of core training to ensure you have the opportunity to thoroughly embed in Ten10 culture, get to know your team and mentors and we can assess your learning style but will have the option to move home and learn remotely for the remainder.After core training is completed, you\u2019ll have a week off training to meet with your assigned career mentor to discuss the areas of Tech you\u2019ve found you love and want to explore further and you will apply for a place on a further training stream that\u2019s suited to you.Stream 1 \u2013 Change Management: Teaching you the skills to become a Business Analyst, Project Manager, Service Desk Analyst, Software Tester or RPA Analyst.Stream 2 \u2013 Platform Engineering: Learn about DevOps and Artificial Intelligence, you could go on to be a DevOps Engineer, Machine Learning Engineer or Cyber Security Analyst.Stream 3 \u2013 Data Engineering: Deep dive into data and learn the skills to be a Data Analyst or Business Intelligence Analyst.Stream 4 \u2013 Software Engineering: This stream is delivered face-to-face from our Leeds office, you\u2019ll learn about test-driven Development, Programming and specialise in a specific language, setting you up for success as a Developer or Technical Tester.Grow ITNext, you\u2019ll have some time for further upskilling and development via self-driven training, lets focus on YOU, would you benefit from some further 1-2-1 training? Would you like to become certified in something? Ten10 will fund your self-development and industry qualifications and you\u2019ll have a mentor to bounce ideas off.Live ITAfter your training is complete, you will begin work on a real time project with one of Ten10\u2019s clients (with lots of support!). We\u2019ll work with you to determine which type of client placementwould suit best (based on your interests, your preference for working environment, skillset post- training and client demand). Our clients include fashion brands, market-leading retailers, departments of the British Government, professional services organisations, charities, healthcare providers, law firms and financial institutions. Our clients are industry leaders and based across England and Scotland; relocation may be required \u2013 but we support you with that financially and pastorally.Gain valuable hands-on experience, take advantage of the continued training and development opportunities, be mentored by industry-leading professionals, and jump headfirst into the Ten10 social scene! Live IT is a continuation of your learning journey, we believe that hands-on experience is the best way to build your skillset. As the two-year Academy comes to an end, you may choose to continue your career with Ten10 in our consultancy or be offered a permanent role with your client.Perks and Benefits\u00a3400 monthly bursary during training, with the offer of free accommodation (& bills). Once you\u2019ve passed training and begun work, your starting salary will be between \u00a325,000 and \u00a328,500 with six-monthly pay increases to support your accelerated career progression and you can expect to be earning a minimum of \u00a340,000 after 2 years.We love a party, and know how to throw one properly, with a graduation bash at the end of your training, a large summer and Christmas events as well as sporadic celebrations and trips throughout the yearQuarterly and annual awards to recognise greatnessVarious charitable initiatives throughout the year, get involved!Free refreshments, fruit and 4pm Friday office drinksThe opportunity to work with a variety of industry-leading, well-known clients across the UK from varying industries (such as: retail, gaming, financial services, professional services, legal, the government)Constant support and care from day one \u2013 a designated career mentor, a line manager, course trainers, Academy buddy scheme and the Academy Wellbeing TeamRegular social meetups across the country with colleaguesLaptop, learning tools and tech kit providedContributory pension scheme, life assurance, sick pay scheme, Medicash healthcare, Bike2Work scheme, relocation support, travel and moving house loanTen10 Stars: you\u2019re gifted \u2018stars\u2019 every month to give to your colleagues for being amazing! Work hard, receive stars, save them up and cash them in for retail vouchers, a charitable contribution or a PayPal balance transfer.\u00a320 monthly gym membership contribution.Ten10 & YouTen10 is a successful, fast-growing technology consultancy with our people at the heart of everything we do; it\u2019s the perfect time to join us and kickstart your career in one of the world\u2019s biggest industries.You don\u2019t need to tick any \u2018technology\u2019 box to be part of the team, take everything you think you know about the industry and throw it away; everyone is welcome, and everyone has something unique to offer.We\u2019d like you to join our team, where your voice will be heard, and your involvement will be valued;Ten10 will be even better once you join us! We can\u2019t wait to meet you!\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Scotland, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": null, "arr": "UNK", "sen_raw": "Entry Level", "sen": "LEVEL_1", "tech_raw": "Software Tester / Business Analyst / Developer / Cyber", "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": "\u00a325,000 and \u00a328,500", "comp": "BELOW_45K"}}
