{"index": 902, "title": "Senior Process Engineer - Water Sector", "job_location": "Newcastle Upon Tyne, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "The OpportunityAre you an experienced Process Engineer ready to take the next bold step in your career?Imagine applying genuinely new ways of working to solve unprecedented industry-wide efficiency and environmental challenges. At Stantec, that's your daily reality. We\u2019re not just designing solutions; we're redefining what's possible in the Water sector.This is about your journey and your impact. We're inviting a Senior Process Engineer\u2014with a strong background in Clean Water or Wastewater treatment\u2014to join our growing, collaborative teams in Newcastle.We\u2019re Looking For You To Lead the Design: Provide process design leadership across diverse, multi-client projects, challenging conventional thinking and driving sustainable outcomes.  Grow Your Expertise: Utilise your experience across the full design life cycle: process modelling, mass balances, P&IDs, control philosophies, and troubleshooting.  Shape the Future: Actively contribute to our teams' digital delivery strategy, leveraging technology to provide superior client solutions.  Mentor and Inspire: Step into a mentorship role, guiding the next generation of Process Engineers and helping them become leaders in their field. Why Stantec? It's About Your Future.We understand that a new role must offer more than a competitive salary\u2014it must accelerate your career and offer genuine growth.You'll tap into Stantec\u2019s global network of experts, exposing you to an incredible variety of projects, clients, and technical frameworks. This is a direct pathway to rapid skill expansion and true technical leadership. We commit to your advancement with industry-leading training, development, and paid professional subscriptions to ensure your continuous journey toward excellence and defined career progression. Mentorship isn't just a requirement; it's a two-way street for growth. Furthermore, you'll join an award-winning culture: we were named International Consulting Firm of the Year and a Best Place to Work (NCE Awards 2024). We support your work-life balance with flexible working arrangements, a competitive salary, free private medical insurance, and generous paid holidays.About YouYou are proven in the Water Sector, having substantial experience delivering process engineering design with a specific focus on either Clean Water or Wastewater treatment.You are likely a Chartered Engineer with a relevant institution (or actively working towards this professional status) and a Collaborative Leader, thriving on working with clients and stakeholders to translate their needs into genuinely innovative and efficient process engineering solutions that exceed expectations.Finally, you are a Digital Advocate, keen to contribute to digital delivery strategies and apply new technological approaches to project outcomes.To hear what some of our employees say about life at Stantec, please click on My Stantec Stories#UKWaterAbout StantecThe Stantec community unites more than 34,000 employees working in over 450 locations across 6 continents. We have been working with our clients and communities in the UK for over 150 years. We plan, design, deliver and manage the development and infrastructure needed to support the creation of sustainable, healthy and prosperous communities.Our teams provide effective and relevant solutions, translating our clients\u2019 vision into valued consents, deliverable plans for projects and programmes, and efficient designs for delivery, based on technical excellence and deep market insights. We deal with today\u2019s challenges, but also keep a fairer, better tomorrow in sight, looking at how we deliver clean growth, support radical changes in our economy and meet the needs of future communities.Stantec provides equal employment opportunities to all qualified employees and applicants for future and current employment and prohibit discrimination on the grounds of race, colour, religion, sex, national origin, age, marital status, genetic information, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or gender expression. We prohibit discrimination in decisions concerning recruitment, hiring, referral, promotion, compensation, fringe benefits, job training, terminations or any other condition of employment. Stantec is in compliance with laws and regulations and ensures equitable opportunities in all aspects of employment.Building an inspired, inclusive work environment that attracts, supports, and develops world-class talent is a crucial key to our success. If you are excited by this role but worry that your experience doesn\u2019t exactly align, we encourage you to apply.At Stantec we want you to perform your best at every stage of the recruitment process and are committed to ensuring it is accessible to all. If you need any support or require adjustments to be made then please contact [email protected] and we will talk to you about how we can support you.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Newcastle Upon Tyne, England, United Kingdom", "loc": "UK_OTHER", "arr_raw": "flexible working arrangements", "arr": "HYBRID", "sen_raw": "Senior", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": null, "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": null, "comp": "NO_GBP"}}
{"index": 903, "title": "Software Engineer", "job_location": "San Francisco, CA", "jd_text": "Founding Software Engineer (Mid\u2013Senior Level)Why ZaniaEvery enterprise spends millions of dollars on Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC). It's one of the most critical, yet universally painful, parts of running a business. For decades, this industry has been dominated by legacy systems with notoriously low NPS scores, making it totally ripe for disruption.Zania is building agentic AI for Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) to solve this massive problem. We are on a rocketship trajectory, creating intelligent agents that automate and augment the most complex risk and compliance workflows. We have found exceptional product-market fit and are scaling our team very quickly. Some reasons to join Zania are:Dream Customers: Our customers are the most notable enterprises in the world, including FAANG, Big 4 firms and a portfolio of top customers. Tier 1 Backing: Funded by a leading Tier 1 venture capital fund, giving us the resources to build a generational company. World-Class Team: Zania is hiring the best. Our team includes AI and Security leaders from Airbnb, Microsoft, Bain & Company, Deloitte, PwC, Brex, and Instacart. Pioneering Technology: Our engineers and GRC experts work at the absolute forefront of applied AI, building the next generation of agentic systems that will define the future of compliance. Hyper-Growth: We have seen 10x ARR growth in the last year and are rapidly expanding. Competitive Compensation & Equity. The Role:As a Software Engineer, you will be a core member of our engineering team, building the backend systems that power both our core product and our agentic AI platform. This is a backend-focused role for engineers who thrive on solving challenges at a massive scale; full-stack experience is a strong plus. You will design, build, and deploy the critical infrastructure and services that handle everything from petabyte-scale data retrieval to running thousand-step AI agents. This is a unique opportunity to tackle some of the most demanding problems in computing today and build systems with government-level security and reliability.What You'll Do:Engineer Core Product Features: Take ownership of building and delivering scalable, secure backend services that directly power our user-facing product. Build Petabyte-Scale AI Pipelines: Design and implement robust systems for retrieval over petabyte-scale document troves and engineer pipelines for large-scale data collection. Develop Advanced Agentic Systems: Build the backend infrastructure for complex, 1000-step planning agents that help companies with critical processes, and create organizational-level interfaces for human-AI collaboration. Contribute to the architecture and management of our cloud infrastructure, ensuring high availability and performance. Engineer systems with the highest standards of security and reliability to protect the world's most sensitive data. What We're Looking For:Experience: 5+ years of professional software engineering experience (not intended for recent graduates). Proven Technical Impact: A demonstrated track record of delivering complex, high-quality backend systems. Product Building Experience: You have a history of building and launching robust products or platforms, ideally in a hyper-growth or 0-to-1 startup environment. Deep Technical Expertise: You are a hands-on, highly technical backend engineer with proficiency in:Python: For building robust backend services and AI pipelines. Large-Scale Systems: Experience with distributed systems, large-scale data processing (e.g., Spark), and cloud platforms (Azure, AWS, GCP). TypeScript and React: Experience is a plus for contributing across the stack but is not required. Ownership and Drive: You take full ownership of your projects, demonstrating a strong bias for action and the ability to manage complex priorities in a fast-paced environment. Pragmatic Problem-Solving: You are a proactive and resourceful problem-solver who is comfortable with ambiguity and sees immense challenges as opportunities for growth. Clear Communication: You can articulate complex technical ideas clearly and persuasively to stakeholders across the organization. Compensation And BenefitsFlexible PTO policy. Medical, dental, and vision insuranceMeals and snacks in the officeRelocation and immigration supportZania is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.Compensation Range: $100K - $200K\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "San Francisco, CA", "loc": "OUTSIDE_UK", "arr_raw": null, "arr": "UNK", "sen_raw": "Founding Software Engineer (Mid\u2013Senior Level)", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "Python, TypeScript, React, AI", "tech": ["REACT", "JS_TS", "AI_ML"], "comp_raw": "Compensation Range: $100K - $200K", "comp": "NO_GBP"}}
